{
  "text": "With the above notations, recall that, for each foliation F on P 2 with a rational first integral, the divisor D F satisfies D 2 F = 0 and D F \u00b7\u1ebc q \u2265 0 for all q \u2208 B F . Also, D F \u00b7\u1ebc q > 0 for all q \u2208 B F \\ N F [CITATION_1] Exer. 7.2] . These facts and Lemma 1 support the following decision algorithm for the problem of deciding whether an arbitrary foliation F has a rational first integral of a fixed degree d. In fact, it allows to compute it in the affirmative case.",
